an>.<span class=\"name\">NormalizePattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">instReprPatternArgKind</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Repr.html#Repr\">Repr</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\">PatternArgKind</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.lean#L624-L636","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.typeFormer","line":624,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.typeFormer","doc":"Types and type formers are mostly ignored during E-matching, and processed using\n`isDefEq`. However, if the argument is of the form `C ..` where `C` is inductive type\nwe process it as part of the pattern. Suppose we have `as bs : List α`, and a pattern\ncandidate expression `as ++ bs`, i.e., `@HAppend.hAppend (List α) (List α) (List α) inst as bs`.\nIf we completely ignore the types, the pattern will just be\n```\n@HAppend.hAppend _ _ _ _ #1 #0\n```\nThis is not ideal because the E-matcher will try it in any goal that contains `++`,\neven if it does not even mention lists.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.typeFormer\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">NormalizePattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">PatternArgKind</span>.<span class=\"name\">typeFormer</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\">PatternArgKind</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.lean#L622-L623","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.proof","line":622,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.proof","doc":"Proofs are ignored during E-matching. Lean is proof irrelevant. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.proof\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">NormalizePattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">PatternArgKind</span>.<span class=\"name\">proof</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\">PatternArgKind</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.lean#L620-L621","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.instImplicit","line":620,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.instImplicit","doc":"Instance implicit arguments are considered support and handled using `isDefEq`. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.instImplicit\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">NormalizePattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">PatternArgKind</span>.<span class=\"name\">instImplicit</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\">PatternArgKind</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.lean#L618-L619","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.relevant","line":618,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.relevant","doc":"Argument is relevant for E-matching. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind.relevant\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">NormalizePattern</span>.<span class=\"name\">PatternArgKind</span>.<span class=\"name\">relevant</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\">PatternArgKind</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.lean#L617-L637","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind","line":617,"kind":"inductive","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/EMatchTheorem.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.NormalizePattern.PatternArgKind\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<